The White House Office of the Press Secretary has released a fact sheet outlining the actions that the Obama administration is taking to protect communities from the impacts of climate change. The fact sheet highlights the health impacts of climate change and emphasizes the need to protect vulnerable populations. The administration is convening stakeholders, identifying solutions to minimize impacts, expanding access to climate and health data, and preparing the next generation of medical and health professionals. The fact sheet also announces the release of a draft Climate and Health Assessment report, executive actions to reduce the health impacts of climate change, and commitments from various organizations and academic institutions to train health professionals to address climate change.